In three weeks’ time, on the 24th of this month, the Harvest Festival will begin. You may remember my report in the first issue of this paper where I sat in on one of the festival committee’s meetings. I've finally gotten the schedule of the events. I wish to remind all that wish to be involved with the baking sale, particularly the houses, need to contact Sheriff Zaria with your entrees. Make sure to come out on and bring your friends, it sure to be a wonderful time!
Lundi 24th (Monday):~Opening Ceremony;~Tourney Begins;
Mardi 25th (Tuesday):~Fashion Show by Esquire Meepers;
Mercredi 26th (Wednesday):~Baking Sale by Acting Sheriff Zaria;
Jeudi 27th (Thursday):~Art Gala by Doctor Hush;
Vendredi 28th (Friday):~Mud Wrestling by Acting Sheriff Zaria;
Samedi 29th (Saturday):~Small/People Auction by Acting Sheriff Zaria;
Dimache 30th (Sunday):~Closing Ceremony
